				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">... Good for C? On an 8-bitter? Er.<br /><br />Just how much cheating is allowed?<br /><br />Can I choose a 16-bit machine that's contemporary? (CP1600) Can I choose an 8-ish-bit machine that's substantially later? (AVR;1996) How about a 16-bit ISA that's older than the AVR? (MSP430;1993) ... How about a 32-bit ISA that's substantially older? (MIPS or ARM; 1985, both with prototypes back to 1980)<br /><br />Honestly, if I wanted to make something &quot;Like the NES, but less bad for C&quot; I'd end up very close to the SMS.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

